learning, and technology.

00:25:04.730 --> 00:25:07.880
On the one hand,
now we know it has

00:25:07.880 --> 00:25:09.821
been a success like
the last five year,

00:25:09.821 --> 00:25:11.070
very interesting developments.

00:25:11.070 --> 00:25:15.010
But learning stayed flat.

00:25:15.010 --> 00:25:18.330
So learning and education
was in bad shape before.

00:25:18.330 --> 00:25:21.590
Now it's worse because everyone
is just looking at the screen.

00:25:21.590 --> 00:25:25.560
And how's transformation
supposed to happen that way?

00:25:25.560 --> 00:25:28.540
So in other words,
it's working well.

00:25:28.540 --> 00:25:30.552
MOOCs are working
well for the transfer

00:25:30.552 --> 00:25:31.510
of technical knowledge.

00:25:31.510 --> 00:25:34.620
It's not working at
all for developing

00:25:34.620 --> 00:25:38.870
these deeper capacities
of innovation leadership.

00:25:38.870 --> 00:25:42.940
So our question was can you
link these two things-- the MOOC

00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:46.060
and democratization
on the one hand,

00:25:46.060 --> 00:25:51.620
and the activation of the
deep learning innovation cycle

00:25:51.620 --> 00:25:54.360
that I indicated before--
opening the mind, the heart,

00:25:54.360 --> 00:25:56.890
the will-- on the other hand?

00:25:56.890 --> 00:25:57.935
That was the experiment.

