00:27:16.670 --> 00:27:19.070
that the big
disruption that's going

00:27:19.070 --> 00:27:21.770
on in the space of learning
that really kind of

00:27:21.770 --> 00:27:25.970
turns that whole
paradigm upside down.

00:27:25.970 --> 00:27:30.900
So what this first
clip really did

00:27:30.900 --> 00:27:36.250
is tell the story of
disruption that I believe

00:27:36.250 --> 00:27:37.830
is currently going
on in the field

00:27:37.830 --> 00:27:42.480
of learning and leadership,
which is two transformations.

00:27:42.480 --> 00:27:46.530
The first transformation
is shifting the outer place

00:27:46.530 --> 00:27:50.600
off learning from the
classroom, listening to folks,

00:27:50.600 --> 00:27:53.790
to the real world,
learning by doing.

00:27:53.790 --> 00:27:57.270
And the second
transformation concerns

00:27:57.270 --> 00:27:59.480
shifting the inner
place of learning

00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:05.400
from the head to the heart,
and from the heart to the head.

00:28:05.400 --> 00:28:08.000
So a more, you
could say, holistic

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:11.610
that's not only
limited here, but that

00:28:11.610 --> 00:28:14.870
includes the emotional
intelligence,

00:28:14.870 --> 00:28:18.700
the relational capacities
on the one hand,

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:23.440
but also the learning by
doing on the other hand.

00:28:23.440 --> 00:28:25.470
And what it really
is organizationally

00:28:25.470 --> 00:28:27.920
is bursting up.

00:28:27.920 --> 00:28:30.280
It's opening the old dome.

00:28:30.280 --> 00:28:32.360
So the old model of
learning, everyone

00:28:32.360 --> 00:28:36.760
is sitting inside that dome,
not a single window outside,

00:28:36.760 --> 00:28:40.310
and you're captured inside
in these classrooms,

00:28:40.310 --> 00:28:43.810
to a more open structure
where people can freely

00:28:43.810 --> 00:28:45.340
move in and out.

